column1: Analysis of the source code shared by the actor
column3: revealed it is a Delphi implementation of code intended to establish a connection with the extensions for financial service (XFS) Manager. XFS Manager is a part of the Windows open system architecture (WOSA) XFS Standard for major ATM vendor compliance (see: http://www.cen.eu/work/areas/ict/ebusiness/pages/ws-xfs.aspx). The XFS Manager is an interface between an application and peripheral devices
column4: in this case, it&rsquo
column6: a cash dispenser. Interaction with the middleware XFS Manager is not unique for this particular ATM malware variant and other strains such as Ploutus and Tyupkin also utilize it.
